                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1"
                        >Baker, Charles</persName>/27: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1" type="from">Adams</persName>) to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-20T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 20, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 20—6:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. My No. 33, February 19, 5 p.m. In response to a request from <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_HC1">Ho Chen Chun</persName> for suggestion of some
                    means of procuring the release of <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1">Captain
                        Baker</persName>, I have replied that my understanding is that the
                    Communists who hold <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1">Baker</persName> are
                    closely identified with Pailochi and that if hostages of some local prominence
                    could be taken from that village <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1">Captain
                        Baker</persName>’s release might be considered effected. General Ho replied
                    that he considered the suggestion practicable and would bear it in mind in
                    dealing with the case.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Adams</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
